>, he became a publisher, retiring recently as editor-in-chief of a London publishing house.</p></div></div></div></div><div class=vertical_module_list_row><h3 class="about_title">Bibliographic information</h3><div class="about_content" id="metadata_content" style="padding-bottom:.3em"><div class="metadata_sectionwrap"><table id="metadata_content_table"><tr class="metadata_row"><td class="metadata_label">Title</td><td class="metadata_value"><span dir=ltr>The Hugo Young Papers: Thirty Years of British Politics - off the record</span></td></tr><tr class="metadata_row"><td class="metadata_label"><span dir=ltr>Author</span></td><td class="metadata_value"><a class="primary" href="https://www.google.com/search?tbo=p&amp;tbm=bks&amp;q=inauthor:%22Hugo+Young%22&amp;source=gbs_metadata_r&amp;cad=6"><span dir=ltr>Hugo Young</span></a></td></tr><tr class="metadata_row"><td class="metadata_label"><span dir=ltr>Editor</span></td><td class="metadata_value"><a class="primary" href="https://www.google.com/search?tbo=p&amp;tbm=bks&amp;q=inauthor:%22Ion+Trewin%22&amp;source=gbs_metadata_r&amp;cad=6"><span dir=ltr>Ion Trewin</span></a></td></tr><tr class="metadata_row"><td class="metadata_label"><span dir=ltr>Publisher</span></td><td class="metadata_value"><span dir=ltr>Penguin UK, 2008</span></td></tr><tr class="metadata_row"><td class="metadata_label"><span dir=ltr>ISBN</span></td><td class="metadata_value"><span dir=ltr>0141903600, 9780141903606</span></td></tr><tr class="metadata_row"><td class="metadata_label"><span dir=ltr>Length</span></td><td class="metadata_value"><span dir=ltr>880 pages</span></td></tr><tr class="metadata_row"><td class="metadata_label"><span dir=ltr>Subjects</span></td><td class="metadata_value"><div style="display:inline" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Breadcrumb"><a class="primary" href="https://www.google.com/search?tbo=p&amp;tbm=bks&amp;q=subject:%22Political+Science%22" itemprop="url" dir=ltr><span itemprop="title">Political Science</sp